content.title: Step 4: Create and Deploy the Lambda Function
content.visibleText:
Step 4: Create and Deploy the Lambda Function

1. Create a Lambda Function:

bash
aws lambda create-function \
--function-name SalesforceQuery \
--runtime python3.8 \ # replace with your Python version
--role arn:aws:iam::your-account-id:role/your-lambda-role \
--handler lambda_function.lambda_handler \
--zip-file fileb://function.zip \
--timeout 15 \
--memory-size 128

Role: Replace `your-account-id` and `your-lambda-role` with the appropriate IAM role ARN that has permissions to execute Lambda functions.

content.title: Create a Deployment Package
content.visibleText:
2. Create a Deployment Package:

bash
cd venv/lib/python3.x/site-packages/ # replace 'python3.x' with your Python version
zip -r9 $(OLDPWD)/function.zip .
cd $OLDPWD
zip -g function.zip lambda_function.py
